Specifically derived from upstream at tag compound-engineering-v3.8.1:

Research agents:
- agents/web-researcher.md (from agents/ce-web-researcher.agent.md;
  changes: renamed `ce-web-researcher` → `web-researcher`; dropped the
  `tools: WebSearch, WebFetch` frontmatter restriction so the agent can
  also write findings to disk when callers ask; removed the Integration
  Points section that referenced upstream skills we don't ship; updated
  the Tool Guidance section to acknowledge optional Write usage)
- agents/best-practices-researcher.md (from agents/ce-best-practices-researcher.agent.md;
  changes: renamed `ce-best-practices-researcher` → `best-practices-researcher`;
  dropped the `tools:` frontmatter restriction; replaced the hardcoded
  ce-* skill-name mappings with a semantic-matching instruction;
  removed the GitHub-issue-specific Special Cases section)

Review skill (slim port of upstream's parallel-review pipeline):
- skills/review/SKILL.md (from skills/ce-code-review/SKILL.md; changes:
  renamed `ce-code-review` → `review`; rewrote the Reviewers section to
  list only the 11 personas we ship instead of upstream's 18 + 4 CE
  agents; removed the CE always-on agent dispatch block (agent-native,
  learnings-researcher) from Stage 4; removed the CE conditional agent
  dispatch block (schema-drift, deployment-verification) from Stage 4;
  removed Stage 5 step 11 "Preserve CE agent artifacts"; removed Stage 6
  output sections 7–10 (Learnings & Past Solutions, Agent-Native Gaps,
  Schema Drift Check, Deployment Notes); pruned the same sections from
  the headless output envelope; replaced run-artifact path
  `/tmp/compound-engineering/ce-code-review/<run-id>/` with
  `/tmp/engineering-loop/review/<run-id>/`; replaced `.context/...`
  artifact path equivalently; removed inert mentions of ce-work, lfg,
  slfg, ce-resolve-pr-feedback, ce-polish-beta from prose; updated
  Stage 3 announce-team example to use our personas; updated Protected
  Artifacts framing to drop the "created by ce-X" attributions)
- skills/review/references/persona-catalog.md (rewritten from
  skills/ce-code-review/references/persona-catalog.md; changes: dropped
  CE always-on agents block, dropped Stack-Specific Conditional section
  entirely, dropped CE Conditional Agents section entirely, added
  code-simplicity to always-on layer, rewrote Selection rules to match
  the 5+6 structure)
- skills/review/references/review-output-template.md (from
  skills/ce-code-review/references/review-output-template.md; changes:
  removed the four bullet-list lines describing Learnings & Past
  Solutions, Agent-Native Gaps, Schema Drift Check, and Deployment Notes
  sections)
